Students matriculated in a regular undergraduate program can qualify for academic honors at the end of the fall and spring semesters if they have completed 12 or more credits used in the calculation of the term GPA, achieved a GPA of 3.00 or better in the semester, have no incomplete, or have any grade lower than a "C" in the semester.
